HEADWORD: Corolliflorous
<hw>Co*rol`li*flo"rous</hw> <pr>(-fl?"r?s)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Corolla</ets> + L. <ets>flos</ets>, <ets>floris</ets>,
flower.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the stamens borne on the
petals, and the latter free from the calyx. Compare
<er>Calycifloral</er> and <er>Thalamifloral</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

